helpdesk-ticket.subject: School of Nursing - simulation
helpdesk-ticket.description:
To whoever,
I tried to connect up the Laerdal Manikin in CC133 for a simulation I will be running Tuesday at 3:00. Here are some problems
1. The program is not picking up/sensing the manikin. It searches, but unable to locate. 2. The video and recording is not connecting up. 3. The phone in the control room in CC133 is not working. I need to use the phone during the simulation on Tuesday
So, is this related to something MSOE is doing with the update? Is it the Laerdal product? The phone is a MSOE thing
Can this be fixed by 3:00 Tuesday? I am teaching from 0800-1000, meeting from 1000-1130, then another meeting at 1300.
Thanks
Jane B. Paige PhD, RN, CNE, CHSE Professor School of Nursing | Undergraduate Program Director MSOE University Milwaukee, WI Office: 414-277-4522 paige@msoe.edu<mailto:paige@msoe.edu> [SON logo]<http://www.msoe.edu/academics/nursing-undergraduate/>[LinkedIN]<https://na01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Fin%2Fjane-b-paige-7820ab54%3Ftrk%3Dnav_responsive_tab_profile_pic&data=02%7C01%7C%7C12f718818ab141fe902708d60168a639%7C4046ceacfdd346c9ac80b7c4a49bab70%7C0%7C0%7C636697946305411494&sdata=Ha7eshvETZDoPNz%2FsrRhSAAqry0jFKQtVrAYZywSpmg%3D&reserved=0> [RGate] <https://na01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.researchgate.net%2Fprofile%2FJane_Paige&data=02%7C01%7C%7C12f718818ab141fe902708d60168a639%7C4046ceacfdd346c9ac80b7c4a49bab70%7C0%7C0%7C636697946305411494&sdata=iIPwZ8RU6Ug5%2FcZMqXm1vXH5wwSKNhk4AjxbiwBDSz0%3D&reserved=0>

helpdesk-ticket.description:
Helpdesk:
Please see email below.
Regarding students unable to print their parking applications.
Lead Communication Officer Willie Lewis MLH - 324 E Juneau Ave. Milwaukee, WI 53202 Monday - Friday 8am - 4pm 414-277-7169 lewisw@msoe.edu<mailto:lewisw@msoe.edu>
From: Fyfe, Billy Sent: Monday, August 13, 2018 5:11 PM To: Bozicevich, Russell <bozicevich@msoe.edu>; Lewis, Willie <lewisw@msoe.edu> Subject: Fwd: 2018-2019 Academic Year Parking
Good afternoon,
When you have a moment, could you please look into this issue? It appears that students cannot print their application because the system is asking them to login.
Thank you both for your assistance!
Director Fyfe
Sent from my iPhone
Begin forwarded message: From: "Kasten, Leslie" <kastenlj@msoe.edu<mailto:kastenlj@msoe.edu>> Date: August 13, 2018 at 5:01:50 PM CDT To: "Fyfe, Billy" <fyfe@msoe.edu<mailto:fyfe@msoe.edu>> Subject: RE: 2018-2019 Academic Year Parking Hello,
I went to fill out the application and when I try to go to the page I print it out and it prompts me to login it says that my username/password is incorrect but I tried all of the passwords I can think of. Is there somewhere I can go to reset my password?
Thanks,
Leslie Kasten
From: Fyfe, Billy Sent: Monday, August 13, 2018 12:30 PM To: All Students <AllStudents@msoe.edu<mailto:AllStudents@msoe.edu>> Cc: PublicSafety-Staff <PublicSafety-Staff@msoe.edu<mailto:PublicSafety-Staff@msoe.edu>> Subject: 2018-2019 Academic Year Parking Importance: High
2018-2019 ACADEMIC YEAR PARKING ONLINE APPLICATIONS NOW OPEN FOR STUDENT PARKING PERMITS AND EVENING PARKING PERMITS
To apply for a 2018-2019 academic year parking permit, please select the link below.
https://app2.omnigo.com/msoe/CESIReportExec/OPR/OPRMain.aspx?IsAuth=1&groupid=110&groupname=PUBLIC+SAFETY+DEPARTMENT<https://na01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fapp2.omnigo.com%2Fmsoe%2FCESIReportExec%2FOPR%2FOPRMain.aspx%3FIsAuth%3D1%26groupid%3D110%26groupname%3DPUBLIC%2BSAFETY%2BDEPARTMENT&data=02%7C01%7C%7Cdbb59abe99b248a74dc708d6016a1c86%7C4046ceacfdd346c9ac80b7c4a49bab70%7C0%7C0%7C636697952587405008&sdata=5qpZDsGxU3zECg0N%2FzRWlj1%2FtIuhOh4zaT56H0qCUwg%3D&reserved=0>
*****When you get to step 4, (Review) please take a moment to make sure the information you’re providing is accurate. At the bottom of step 4, you’ll notice the “View Permit Registration” field. Please select this field and print your parking permit application. Please bring your parking permit application with you when you pick up your parking permit at the Public Safety Command Center. The Public Safety Command Center is located on the ground floor of the MLH residence hall, 324 East Juneau Avenue.*****
2018-2019 Academic Year Student Parking Permits $495.00, for 24-hours, 7 day-a-week parking for the entire 2018-2019 academic year (September 2018 through May 2019). You can pick up your Student parking permit beginning Monday, August 20, 2018. Once you apply for your parking permit online, please report to the Public Safety Command Center, located at 324 E. Juneau Avenue, to finalize your payment and to pick up your Student parking permit.
2018-2019 Academic Year Evening Parking Permits Students taking evening classes at MSOE may park free-of-charge starting after 4:00 p.m. You can pick up your Evening parking permit beginning Monday, August 20, 2018. Once you apply for your Evening parking permit online, please report to the Public Safety Command Center, located at 324 E. Juneau Avenue, to pick up your Evening parking permit. You must bring a copy of your class schedule showing you are registered for an evening class to obtain an Evening Parking Permit.
2018-2019 Academic Year Motorcycle/Moped Parking For both day and evening hours, motorcycles and mopeds do not require a parking permit, but they must be registered or re-registered each academic year with the Public Safety Department. Motorcycles/mopeds may only be parked in the designated motorcycle/moped areas at the west end of the State Street A parking lot, located at 501 East State Street, and the east end of the Broadway parking lot, located at 1036 N. Broadway. There is also indoor motorcycle/moped parking in the Campus Center underground garage and also the Viets Field parking complex for $75 per quarter. Motorcycles/mopeds not registered with the Public Safety Department or parked in any other campus areas are subject to a citation, without warning. Due to snow removal, there is no overnight motorcycle/moped on the two outdoor motorcycle/moped parking areas from the last day of the fall quarter to April 1st.
Viets Field Parking Complex Bike Corral Usage Secure and covered bicycle parking on the Market Level of the Viets Field parking complex. While this bicycle parking is free-of-charge, bicycles parked in the bike corral must be registered with the Public Safety Department. You may register your bicycle at any time by coming to the MSOE Public Safety Department Command Center, located at 324 E. Juneau Avenue (Margaret Loock Hall).
If you have any questions regarding parking for the 2018-2019 academic year, please feel free to contact me.
Thank you, Billy Fyfe
Billy Fyfe Director of Public Safety Milwaukee School of Engineering 1025 N. Broadway Milwaukee, WI 53202 414.277.2339 (Office) 414.345.7615 (Cell) fyfe@msoe.edu<mailto:fyfe@msoe.edu>

2018-2019 ACADEMIC YEAR PARKING
ONLINE APPLICATIONS NOW OPEN FOR STUDENT PARKING PERMITS AND EVENING PARKING PERMITS
 
 
To apply for a 2018-2019 academic year parking permit, please select the link below.
 
https://app2.omnigo.com/msoe/CESIReportExec/OPR/OPRMain.aspx?IsAuth=1&groupid=110&groupname=PUBLIC+SAFETY+DEPARTMENT
 
*****When you get to step 4, (Review) please take a moment to make sure the information you’re providing is accurate.  At the bottom of step 4, you’ll notice the “View Permit Registration” field.  Please select this field and print your parking permit application.  Please bring your parking permit application with you when you pick up your parking permit at the Public Safety Command Center.  The Public Safety Command Center is located on the ground floor of the MLH residence hall, 324 East Juneau Avenue.*****
 
2018-2019 Academic Year Student Parking Permits
$495.00, for 24-hours, 7 day-a-week parking for the entire 2018-2019 academic year (September 2018 through May 2019).  You can pick up your Student parking permit beginning Monday, August 20, 2018.  Once you apply for your parking permit online, please report to the Public Safety Command Center, located at 324 E. Juneau Avenue, to finalize your payment and to pick up your Student parking permit.
 
2018-2019 Academic Year Evening Parking Permits
Students taking evening classes at MSOE may park free-of-charge starting after 4:00 p.m.  You can pick up your Evening parking permit beginning Monday, August 20, 2018.  Once you apply for your Evening parking permit online, please report to the Public Safety Command Center, located at 324 E. Juneau Avenue, to pick up your Evening parking permit. You must bring a copy of your class schedule showing you are registered for an evening class to obtain an Evening Parking Permit.
 
2018-2019 Academic Year Motorcycle/Moped Parking
For both day and evening hours, motorcycles and mopeds do not require a parking permit, but they must be registered or re-registered each academic year with the Public Safety Department. Motorcycles/mopeds may only be parked in the designated motorcycle/moped areas at the west end of the State Street A parking lot, located at 501 East State Street, and the east end of the Broadway parking lot, located at 1036 N. Broadway. There is also indoor motorcycle/moped parking in the Campus Center underground garage and also the Viets Field parking complex for $75 per quarter. Motorcycles/mopeds not registered with the Public Safety Department or parked in any other campus areas are subject to a citation, without warning. Due to snow removal, there is no overnight motorcycle/moped on the two outdoor motorcycle/moped parking areas from the last day of the fall quarter to April 1st.
 
Viets Field Parking Complex Bike Corral Usage
Secure and covered bicycle parking on the Market Level of the Viets Field parking complex. While this bicycle parking is free-of-charge, bicycles parked in the bike corral must be registered with the Public Safety Department. You may register your bicycle at any time by coming to the MSOE Public Safety Department Command Center, located at 324 E. Juneau Avenue (Margaret Loock Hall).
 
If you have any questions regarding parking for the 2018-2019 academic year, please feel free to contact me.
 
Thank you,
Billy Fyfe
 
 
Billy Fyfe
Director of Public Safety
Milwaukee School of Engineering
1025 N. Broadway
Milwaukee, WI 53202

414.345.7615 (Cell)
fyfe@msoe.edu

helpdesk-ticket.subject: new faculty member in the math department
helpdesk-ticket.description:
We have a new full-time faculty member in the math department, Dr. Yu-sin Chang. Her office will be L-321.
She will need a computer (the X360 Elite) and to have her phone installed. Currently we have Ron Nelson in the office, but he will be moved to a different office, L-315. Dr. Jorgensen is retiring and will vacate L-315 by next week. It is probably best to move Ron Nelson’s phone to L-315 and move the phone from L-315 to L-321 to be used by Chang. Please let me know as soon as the computer is ready so Dr. Chang can start preparing for her classes, etc. Thank you,
Matey Kaltchev, Ph.D. Professor and Chair Department of Physics and Chemistry Department of Mathematics Phone: (414) 277-7544 Milwaukee School of Engineering

helpdesk-note.body:
Sorry for the delay in responding. Shortly after sending you the email, I disappeared into the wilderness with no email, cell phone, or internet.
I do have the Box drive installed on my MSOE computer.
I found that I did not have access to my files which are all in my box file on my MSOE computer when I was off campus and not logged into the internet. When I am logged into the internet or on campus, it appears that the files are on my hard drive. When I was not logged into the internet, they appeared not to be on my computer.
I do want to have access to my files on my MSOE computer when I am not logged onto the internet, and allow Box to sync up once I am logged in.
This is the issue.
My MSOE computer is now at MSOE and I am at home.
Prof. Gonwa
________________________________

The following programs will be offered, with all badge requirements completed during the session: Designing Robots (Brownies - Designing Robots Badge) Think Outside the Brownie Box (Brownies - Inventor Badge) Entertainment Technology (Juniors - Entertainment Technology Badge) Designing Robots (Juniors - Designing Robots Badge) Special Agent (Cadettes - Special Agent Badge) From the Ground Up (Cadettes - Entrepreneur Badge) Registration is through Girl Scouts of Wisconsin Southeast (GSWISE).   4. Page overall text (see below)

Girl Scout  STEM Day

MSOE Todd Wehr Conference Center
Oct. 27, 2018
9 a.m. - 2 p.m.
This event is open to all Girl Scouts! With sessions led by industry professionals along with MSOE students & faculty, girls will get the opportunity to earn badges while getting the collegiate experience.

The following programs will be offered, with all badge requirements completed during the session:
  • Designing Robots (Brownies - Designing Robots Badge)
  • Think Outside the Brownie Box (Brownies - Inventor Badge)
  • Entertainment Technology (Juniors - Entertainment Technology Badge)
  • Designing Robots (Juniors - Designing Robots Badge)
  • Special Agent (Cadettes - Special Agent Badge)
  • From the Ground Up (Cadettes - Entrepreneur Badge)
Registration is through Girl Scouts of Wisconsin Southeast (GSWISE). Check back here for a link when registration opens!

helpdesk-note.body: Hi Brendan Monahan, Issue: https://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/33101 I'm emailing you back for some additional information as we have identified that this is a widespread issue among many staff members. We'd like all staff that are affected to send in the following information to us. Please complete the following steps to send information to us: 1. Search for and open the application called Command Prompt (cmd) 2. Type in the command "ipconfig /all" 3. Take a screenshot of the results that appear in the window. When you take the screenshot, please make sure the entire output from the command is visible. You're able to take a screen shot by completing these steps: 1. Search for and open the application called Snipping Tool 2. Click on the New button with a scissor icon next to it. This will allow you to highlight an area and take a screenshot by dragging over the area 3. Let go of the mouse to let the screenshot be generated. This will open a new window with the screenshot in it. You can right click on the image generated to paste it into Outlook to send as a response to this ticket. Additional information that we would like from you or your other staff would be: - The building you are located in (CC for HR) - The time the issue occurred (Times it was tried to be accessed at) - The room you are located in (The temporary room by the nursing space. If there is a room number associated with this room that would be very beneficial as well) - If you are connected to the internet via WiFi or wired in to the wall - If it is possible for you to see what port the ethernet (internet) cable is plugged in to (it may run from your computer to the wall, or from your phone to the wall) please let us know as well This diagnostic information will be incredibly helpful in helping our vendor identify the issue and correct it. Please send it to us at your earliest convenience! Cheers, Austin Rovge (414) 277 7288 Submit a Ticket: helpdesk@msoe.edu Monday – Friday 8:00 AM – 4:30 PM Saturday and Sunday CLOSED
helpdesk-note.body-html:
Hi Brendan Monahan,

Issue: https://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/33101

I'm emailing you back for some additional information as we have identified that this is a widespread issue among many staff members. We'd like all staff that are affected to send in the following information to us. Please complete the following steps to send information to us:
1. Search for and open the application called Command Prompt (cmd) 
2. Type in the command "ipconfig /all"
3. Take a screenshot of the results that appear in the window. When you take the screenshot, please make sure the entire output from the command is visible.

You're able to take a screen shot by completing these steps:
1. Search for and open the application called Snipping Tool
2. Click on the New button with a scissor icon next to it. This will allow you to highlight an area and take a screenshot by dragging over the area
3. Let go of the mouse to let the screenshot be generated. This will open a new window with the screenshot in it.

You can right click on the image generated to paste it into Outlook to send as a response to this ticket.

Additional information that we would like from you or your other staff would be:
- The building you are located in (CC for HR)
- The time the issue occurred (Times it was tried to be accessed at)
- The room you are located in (The temporary room by the nursing space. If there is a room number associated with this room that would be very beneficial as well)
- If you are connected to the internet via WiFi or wired in to the wall
- If it is possible for you to see what port the ethernet (internet) cable is plugged in to (it may run from your computer to the wall, or from your phone to the wall) please let us know as well

This diagnostic information will be incredibly helpful in helping our vendor identify the issue and correct it. Please send it to us at your earliest convenience!
Cheers,
Austin Rovge

helpdesk-note.body-html:
Hi Brendan Monahan,

Issue: https://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/33101
I'm checking in a final time to see if you are still experiencing issues with RDP and Jenzabar. If so, please follow the instructions and address the questions that were previously sent to you and included again below:

1. Search for and open the application called Command Prompt (cmd) 
2. Type in the command "ipconfig /all"
3. Take a screenshot of the results that appear in the window. When you take the screenshot, please make sure the entire output from the command is visible.
 
You're able to take a screen shot by completing these steps:
1. Search for and open the application called Snipping Tool
2. Click on the New button with a scissor icon next to it. This will allow you to highlight an area and take a screenshot by dragging over the area
3. Let go of the mouse to let the screenshot be generated. This will open a new window with the screenshot in it.
 
You can right click on the image generated to paste it into Outlook to send as a response to this ticket.
 
Additional information that we would like from you or your other staff would be:
- The building you are located in (CC for HR)
- The time the issue occurred (Times it was tried to be accessed at)
- The room you are located in (The temporary room by the nursing space. If there is a room number associated with this room that would be very beneficial as well)

On Wed, 8 Aug at 10:59 AM , Rebecca <gonwarn@msoe.edu<mailto:gonwarn@msoe.edu>> wrote:
Hello IT Department
Please post the Office Assistant position for the Registrar’s office under the Student Employment page. A description for the position is listed below.
Office Assistant – Registrar’s Office The Office Assistant will serve as the point of contact for office visitors; students, faculty, staff, and guests where you will assist with the registration, requests, and inquiries. The Office Assistant will provide support to the Registrar’s staff with day-to-day tasks, including but not limited to: answering incoming phone calls, processing transcript requests, filing, assisting with student registration, and data entry. Assorted additional projects from department staff as assigned. Applicants should maintain a pleasant and helpful attitude toward students, faculty, and incoming guests. Greeting guests or students to help assist them will be a large part of your job description. You will be learning important deadlines and academic processes that you may already have knowledge of in order to better assist student inquiries. You will also receive training in Jenzabar, our software that maintains our student records, in order to assist with processing student requests and data entry. A strong attention to detail, and the ability to work independently (i.e. self-motivated) is important for this position. This position does require some lifting and physical activity. Rebecca Gonwa gonwarn@msoe.edu<mailto:gonwarn@msoe.edu> (414) 277-2291 Academic Year 2018-2019

helpdesk-note.body: Hi Tara, I spoke with Stacey and she mentioned you would be entering three reqs to break up the price. That is the way to go. Jenzabar support confirmed that the column size was the issue. Other institutions have had to break up reqs into smaller amounts. I can't say exactly how the $30 million requisition was handled previously. That req information is not in this specific table. It is possible the table structure has changed over the years or that it was processed differently by Finance at that time. Jenzabar is aware of the need for expanding that field but they do not have it scheduled in any upcoming updates. I went ahead and added MSOE to the list of institutions requesting the size increase. Thanks, Jasmine
helpdesk-note.body-html:
Hi Tara, 

I spoke with Stacey and she mentioned you would be entering three reqs to break up the price. That is the way to go. Jenzabar support confirmed that the column size was the issue. Other institutions have had to break up reqs into smaller amounts. 

I can't say exactly how the $30 million requisition was handled previously. That req information is not in this specific table. It is possible the table structure has changed over the years or that it was processed differently by Finance at that time. 

Jenzabar is aware of the need for expanding that field but they do not have it scheduled in any upcoming updates. I went ahead and added MSOE to the list of institutions requesting the size increase. 

Thanks, 
Jasmine

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Rebecca Gonwa, Issue: https://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/33155 Is your computer opening PDFs in a web browser? Microsoft Edge (default web browser in Windows 10) also acts as the default PDF reader. You can change the default by following these instructions: Install your preferred PDF program (Adobe Acrobat, Foxit, etc) 1) Click on the Start Menu 2) Search for "Default App Settings" and open the program 3) Scroll down to the bottom and click "Choose default apps by file type" (should be the third option from the bottom) 4) Scroll down until you see ".pdf" as the file type on the left 5) Then click on the program to the right of it (or "Choose a default" if it does not have one) and select the program you want to open PDFs with by default Respectfully, Daniel Griffith (414) 277 7288

helpdesk-ticket.subject: Rescinding Emails
helpdesk-ticket.description:
Good evening,
One of our staff members sent an email to a student with an incorrect (and PII sensitive) document attached. She rescinded the email and spoke with the student on the phone about deleting the email, but I have some questions I would like to have answered so we know what steps to take now.
1. Does rescinding an email through Outlook make it so the student cannot view the email or forward it to anyone? 2. Does the student have to actively agree to an email rescind? 3. Can we verify if a student has deleted an item through Outlook? 4. Can we verify if a student has forwarded an item through Outlook?
Any guidance you can provide is much appreciated.
I will be out of the office tomorrow (August 15th), so I have included our Associate Director, Steve Midthun, in this email as well.
Thank you,
[cid:image002.jpg@01D433F9.94967A70]Lena Scheibengraber | Senior Counselor & V.A. Certifying Official MSOE Student Financial Services Financial Aid Office 1025 N Broadway |Milwaukee, WI 53202 Office: 414-277-7223 | Direct: 414-277-7221 Office Hours: Monday – Friday 8:00am – 4:30pm

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Lena Scheibengraber, When rescinding an email in Outlook there's an option to receive a confirmation if the rescind succeeds. If there was no success notification sent the message was not rescinded. If you can provide me with the username of who sent and received the email I can check if it still exists but I likely will not be able to tell if the recipient read the email. Thanks, Chris Hougard MSOE IT Issue: https://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/33188 Good evening,
One of our staff members sent an email to a student with an incorrect (and PII sensitive) document attached. She rescinded the email and spoke with the student on the phone about deleting the email, but I have some questions I would like to have answered so we know what steps to take now.
Does rescinding an email through Outlook make it so the student cannot view the email or forward it to anyone? Does the student have to actively agree to an email rescind?
Can we verify if a student has deleted an item through Outlook? Can we verify if a student has forwarded an item through Outlook?
Any guidance you can provide is much appreciated.
I will be out of the office tomorrow (August 15th), so I have included our Associate Director, Steve Midthun, in this email as well.
Thank you,
Lena Scheibengraber | Senior Counselor & V.A. Certifying Official
MSOE Student Financial Services
Financial Aid Office
1025 N Broadway |Milwaukee, WI 53202 Office: 414-277-7223 | Direct: 414-277-7221 Office Hours: Monday – Friday 8:00am – 4:30pm
Ticket attachments : 1. image001.png
helpdesk-note.body-html:
Hi Lena Scheibengraber,

When rescinding an email in Outlook there's an option to receive a confirmation if the rescind succeeds. If there was no success notification sent the message was not rescinded. If you can provide me with the username of who sent and received the email I can check if it still exists but I likely will not be able to tell if the recipient read the email.

Thanks,

Chris Hougard
MSOE IT

helpdesk-note.body: If he creates a rule in Outlook, to transfer existing emails the customer received/sent the customer would only have to select "Send/Receive All Folders" under the Send/Receive tab. 1. Outlook>File>Manage Rules & Alerts>New Rule 2. Select "Apply rule on messages I receive" and select Next (if for sent emails choose "Apply rule on messages I send") 3. Select Next through the Select Condition(s) step 4. Select "forward it to people or public group" 5. Click on "people or public group" in the Edit rule description box 6. Enter the email you want to forward emails to and select OK 7. Select Finish 8. Go to the Send/Receive tab and select Send/Receive All Folders to have existing emails forwarded
helpdesk-note.body-html:
If he creates a rule in Outlook, to transfer existing emails the customer received/sent the customer would only have to select "Send/Receive All Folders" under the Send/Receive tab.
1. Outlook>File>Manage Rules & Alerts>New Rule
2. Select "Apply rule on messages I receive" and select Next (if for sent emails choose "Apply rule on messages I send")
3. Select Next through the Select Condition(s) step
4. Select "forward it to people or public group"
5. Click on "people or public group" in the Edit rule description box 
6. Enter the email you want to forward emails to and select OK
7. Select Finish 
8. Go to the Send/Receive tab and select Send/Receive All Folders to have existing emails forwarded

helpdesk-note.body-html:

We'd also like some additional diagnostic information from the account staff. The more staff members we can have send in information about this issue, the better. I've detailed some instructions below on how to obtain the information and what we would like:
 
1. Search for and open the application called Command Prompt (cmd) 
2. Type in the command ipconfig /all
3. Take a screenshot of the results that appear in the window. When you take the screenshot, please make sure the entire output from the command is visible.

You're able to take a screen shot by completing these steps:

1. Search for and open the application called Snipping Tool
2. Click on the New button with a scissor icon next to it. This will allow you to highlight an area and take a screenshot by dragging over the area
3. Let go of the mouse to let the screenshot be generated. This will open a new window with the screenshot in it.

You can right click on the image generated to paste it into Outlook to send as a response to this ticket.

Additional information that we would like from you would be:
- The building you are located in
- The time the issue occurred
- The room you are located in
- If you are connected to the internet via WiFi or wired in to the wall
- If it is possible for you to see what port the ethernet (internet) cable is plugged in to (it may run from your computer to the wall, or from your phone to the wall) please let us know as well

Subject: Re: [#INC-33269] Jenzabar Today
 
Hi Joanne Smith,

Issue: https://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/33269
 
We'd also like some additional diagnostic information from the account staff. The more staff members we can have send in information about this issue, the better. I've detailed some instructions below on how to obtain the information and what we would like:
 
1. Search for and open the application called Command Prompt (cmd) 
2. Type in the command ipconfig /all
3. Take a screenshot of the results that appear in the window. When you take the screenshot, please make sure the entire output from the command is visible.
 
You're able to take a screen shot by completing these steps:
 
1. Search for and open the application called Snipping Tool
2. Click on the New button with a scissor icon next to it. This will allow you to highlight an area and take a screenshot by dragging over the area
3. Let go of the mouse to let the screenshot be generated. This will open a new window with the screenshot in it.
 
You can right click on the image generated to paste it into Outlook to send as a response to this ticket.
 
Additional information that we would like from you would be:
- The building you are located in
- The time the issue occurred
- The room you are located in
- If you are connected to the internet via WiFi or wired in to the wall
- If it is possible for you to see what port the ethernet (internet) cable is plugged in to (it may run from your computer to the wall, or from your phone to the wall) please let us know as well
 
This diagnostic information will be incredibly helpful in helping our vendor identify the issue and correct it. Please send it to us at your earliest convenience!
 
Cheers,
Austin Rovge
 
(414) 277 7288

helpdesk-note.body: Hi Davinci Wallace, Issue: https://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/33273 Could you please try the steps below to share the calendar? You should have the rights to do this, if an error pops up please send us a screenshot of it so we could troubleshoot for you. Or we could setup a time to meet at some point this week [except laptop handout days which are Tuesday and Wednesday]. Inside outlook from your Calendar folder, on the Home menu, select Share Calendar. Choose the calendar you want to share from the drop-down menu. In the Calendar Properties dialog box, click Add. You can search for people from your address book or type in their email addresses in the Add box. When you're done adding names in the Add Users dialog box, click OK. Back in the Calendar Properties dialog box, select the person's name or email address, then choose the level of details that you want to share with the person, then click OK. The person you've shared your calendar with will receive a sharing invitation by email. Once the recipient clicks Accept, they'll see your shared calendar in their calendar list. Respectfully, Karolina Klimont TIER 2 SUPPORT TEAM (414) 277-2833 Submit a Service Request: helpdesk@msoe.edu
helpdesk-note.body-html:
Hi Davinci Wallace,

Issue: https://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/33273
Could you please try the steps below to share the calendar? You should have the rights to do this, if an error pops up please send us a screenshot of it so we could troubleshoot for you. Or we could setup a time to meet at some point this week [except laptop handout days which are Tuesday and Wednesday].

  • Inside outlook from your Calendar folder, on the Home menu, select Share Calendar. 
  • Choose the calendar you want to share from the drop-down menu. 
  • In the Calendar Properties dialog box, click Add. 
  • You can search for people from your address book or type in their email addresses in the Add box. When you're done adding names in the Add Users dialog box, click OK. 
  • Back in the Calendar Properties dialog box, select the person's name or email address, then choose the level of details that you want to share with the person, then click OK. 
  • The person you've shared your calendar with will receive a sharing invitation by email. 
  • Once the recipient clicks Accept, they'll see your shared calendar in their calendar list.

Respectfully,
Karolina Klimont
TIER 2 SUPPORT TEAM
(414) 277-2833

helpdesk-note.body: Hi Hanna Dowdy, Issue: https://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/33262 I'm calling you back to ask for some additional information. We'd like all staff that are affected to send in the information to us. Please complete the following steps to send information to us: 1. Search for and open the application called Command Prompt (cmd) 2. Type in the command ipconfig /all 3. Take a screenshot of the results that appear in the window. When you take the screenshot, please make sure the entire output from the command is visible. You're able to take a screen shot by completing these steps: 1. Search for and open the application called Snipping Tool 2. Click on the New button with a scissor icon next to it. This will allow you to highlight an area and take a screenshot by dragging over the area 3. Let go of the mouse to let the screenshot be generated. This will open a new window with the screenshot in it. You can right click on the image generated to paste it into Outlook to send as a response to this ticket. helpdesk-note.body: Hi Chase Harrington, Issue: https://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/33295 Can you let us know what you will all be using macros for? We are concerned because allowing macros creates a security vulnerability in which arbitrary code can be maliciously run in various Office applications. Due to this, we generally only like to allow macros for those who can't get around using them. Apologies for the inconvenience. Respectfully, Alexander Schroeder Assistant Systems Administrator 414.277.7288 Submit a Service Request: helpdesk@msoe.edu "We are building a culture of exceptional customer service!"
helpdesk-note.body-html:
Hi Chase Harrington,

Issue: https://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/33295

Can you let us know what you will all be using macros for?  We are concerned because allowing macros creates a security vulnerability in which arbitrary code can be maliciously run in various Office applications.  Due to this, we generally only like to allow macros for those who can't get around using them.  Apologies for the inconvenience.

Respectfully,
Alexander Schroeder
Assistant Systems Administrator
414.277.7288
Submit a Service Request: helpdesk@msoe.edu
 
"We are building a culture of exceptional customer service!"

helpdesk-note.body:
We are using macros for two things right now, but I am certain they will be used more frequently in the future. First, we are updating our metrology software to automatically create statistical process control spreadsheets. Every user will need to have macros enabled in order to use our metrology software, which is something we do every day. Second, we are using macros to process very large amounts of material data that would be impossible to do by hand (I.e., creating hundreds of charts and checking correlation). Right now we have two computers that have access to macros, so we are having to switch workstations to get things done and it's making things difficult for us. Allowing the employees to all have macro access would help us a lot. If there's anything else you need, let me know.
--Chase Harrington
